      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (normalised index of hemolysis) directly maps to the clinical endpoint of red blood cell damage used in device labelling.",
      "rationale": "NIH was selected as the QoI; however, the linkage to in-vivo RBC damage thresholds relevant to VAD patients has not been formally established in the evidence package."
